    "comment": "Rationale: Using an specific antibody with knockout controls in STED microscopy, it is demonstrated that RIM-BP2 is localized in close proximity to Bassoon and Munc13-1. This shows that RIM-BP2 is localized to the active zone. This finding is in good agreement with STED microscopy performed in the fly NMJ (Liu et.al. 2011).\n\n3/2/2017 Pim\n- Fig 3: STED\n- S2G: EM. Experimental description: KO Mouse Generation.\n\nRIM-BP2 and RIM-BP1 targeting vector construction and KO mouse generation by standard homologous recombination were performed by genOway.",
